          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">
      China-South Korea reset
          </h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/xi-south-korea-strategic-cooperation-certainty-call.jpg" alt="Xi urged the two countries to inject more certainty into regional and international situations and to elevate their strategic cooperation" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>
         Xi urged the two countries to inject more certainty into regional and international situations and to elevate their strategic cooperation. Credits: Korea Pro</i></p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        Chinese President Xi Jinping spoke with South Korea's newly elected President, Lee Jae-myung, and called for <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-11-jun-25-spotlight-h1-1-better-cooperation" target="_blank">better cooperation</a>. Xi urges his support for multilateralism and open trade to maintain global stability, noting that strong ties could promote peace. He also wants to see them protect global supply chains. </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
      This follows Lee’s recent election victory, suggesting a potential shift in Seoul’s foreign policy. South Korean foreign policy tends to lean more towards the US and Japan, a trend that was evident under former president Yoon Suk Yeol. The deterioration in US ties stemmed from the deployment of a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-11-jun-25-spotlight-h1-2-us-missile-defense-system" target="_blank">US missile defense system</a> in South Korea in 2017.</p>
         <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        Although Lee recognizes China as a vital trading partner, he has faced criticism for not taking a firmer stance on security matters, such as the Taiwan Strait issue. </p>
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
        Meanwhile, Lee still prioritizes South Korea’s <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-11-jun-25-spotlight-h1-3-relationship-with-japan" target="_blank">relationship with Japan</a> and agreed on a joint response to challenges from the mutual national interests, exploring ways to coexist. </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
