      <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/global-strategic-alliance-map-us-asia-europe-africa.jpg" alt="Map highlighting strategic global connections with flags of the U.S., Mexico, Poland, Israel, Djibouti, Yemen, and South Korea" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
      <mj-spacer height="10px"/>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-top:4px;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>🇲🇽 Mexico - President condemns violence.</strong> Mexican President Claudia Sheinbaum condemned violence during immigration protests in Los Angeles. She urged Mexican nationals to remain peaceful and prevent provocation. She defends the human rights of Mexicans, regardless of status, and calls for due process in US immigration procedures (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-11-jun-25-worldwide-9-us-mexican-relations" target="_blank">US-Mexican relations</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>🇮🇱 Israel - Greta deported.</strong> Greta Thunberg was deported from Israel after being detained aboard a Gaza-bound aid ship seized by Israeli forces in international waters. Upon arriving in France, Thunberg accused Israel of kidnapping. Israel claimed the mission violated its naval blockade (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-11-jun-25-worldwide-10-greta-s-return" target="_blank">Greta’s return</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
           <strong>🇾🇪 Yemen - Direct attack.</strong> Israel's navy conducted its first-ever direct attack against the Iran-aligned Houthi rebels, targeting docks in Yemen's Hodeida port. The Houthis, in retaliation, have launched missiles and drones at Israel, including attacks on commercial vessels (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-11-jun-25-worldwide-11-about-the-attack" target="_blank">about the attack</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
          <strong>🇩🇯 Djibouti - Stranded deportees.</strong> Eight deportees and 13 ICE officers have been stranded at a US naval base in Djibouti since May, after a court halted their deportation to South Sudan. Held in a converted shipping container, they face harsh conditions, including illness from suspected bacterial infections, high temperatures, and minimal resources (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-11-jun-25-worldwide-12-botched-deportations" target="_blank">botched deportations</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;padding-bottom:6px;">
          <strong>🇰🇷 South Korea - Agreement with Poland.</strong> South Korea is nearing the final stages of negotiations to supply Poland with K2 tanks, building on a $13.7 B arms agreement from 2022. The potential agreement, valued at $6B, involves South Korea’s Hyundai Rotem producing 117 tanks, with 63 to be made locally in Poland (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-11-jun-25-worldwide-13-korean-polish-production" target="_blank">Korean-Polish production</a>).
          </p>
          
         
